      <hedline>
        <hl1>Let's Make Windmills Hip</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''An Old Steel Mill Retools to Produce Clean Energy'' (news article, May 22): The community in Lackawanna, N.Y., should be applauded for its use of wind power to revitalize contaminated land.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''An Old Steel Mill Retools to Produce Clean Energy'' (news article, May 22): The community in Lackawanna, N.Y., should be applauded for its use of wind power to revitalize contaminated land.</p>
        <p>But until we can convince people that alternate energy is both essential and hip, rather than an eyesore, we will be condemned to keep gorging on fossil fuels.</p>
        <p>A suggestion: instead of calling them windmills, let's color coordinate them (in bright pastels or something) and call them moving, Art Deco sculpture gardens.</p>
        <p>Put a few of those out in the Hamptons, and everyone will want a backyard full of them.</p>
        <p>Rick White  New York, May 22, 2007</p>
      </block>
